{
  "_comment": "Single source of truth for the release build matrix (CUDA x PyTorch x Python). pytorch_compatibility mirrors PyTorch's official Release Compatibility Matrix and gates which (cuda, torch, python) triples are allowed; enforced by `python scripts/release_matrix.py validate`. manylinux images verified against sameli/manylinux-cuda on Docker Hub (2026-06-10). Consumers resolve the compound group id `<target>-torch<compact>` (e.g. cu126-torch280) via scripts/release_matrix.py; the publish.yml build matrix is generated by `gen-matrix`. A target may set `gcc_toolset` (e.g. cu126 needs GCC 13 because CUDA 12.6 rejects the manylinux_2_34 image's default GCC 14); ci/setup_compiler.sh installs it and publish.yml prepends it to PATH/LD_LIBRARY_PATH.",
